item.title: Monocle - Reverse Graph Embeddings
item.description: Everything is Not What They Seem More than just a throwback to Wizards of Waverly Place, this statement is fundamental to the way our world operates. Specifically, it hints at the existance of a hidden dimension, a latent space that exists beneath the surface of our reality. And in my opinion, I think that the models surrounding these latent spaces are quite neat: they hint at the idea that there exists a fundamental discrepancy between what is overtly shown and how these patterns come to be.
